-- Moody’s Cuts Glorious Property’s Corporate, Bond Ratings
-- B y   R a c h e l   E v a n s
-- 2012-02-27T12:07:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-27/moody-s-cuts-glorious-property-s-corporate-bond-ratings.html
Glorious Property Holdings Ltd. (845)  had
its corporate and bond ratings cut by Moody’s Investors Service
because of refinancing risks, according to an e-mailed statement
from the ratings company.  Moody’s lowered Glorious Property’s corporate family rating
to B3 from B2, and downgraded the rating on company’s $300
million 13 percent bond due 2015 to Caa1, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  